description._content: Description: Damascus Gate - Showing the Shops which hide the City Walls. Location: Jerusalem, Palestine Date: 1918 Description: Jaffa Gate - Site of proposed "Place" showing the Shops which hide the City Walls. The Blue line refers to the Scheme. Location: Jerusalem, Palestine Date: 1918 Description: Jaffa Gate - Showing the German Emperor's Entrance and the Clock Tower (See Detail Plan No 1 of proposed Restoration). Location: Jerusalem, Palestine Date: 1918 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/743 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
